Well to make the parallel complete let's look at an alternant history timeline<br>
<br>
First the US needs to show a propensity to use weapons of mass destruction.  The Cuban Americans of Florida demonstrate against US government policy, so the National guard is ordered to shell them with VX gas.<br>
<br>
A few years later feeling the pinch in it's wine and cheese exports, the US invades, pillages and plunders a Canadian allied state. Hmmm, let's go with say...France. Then Canada (a major importer of wine and cheese) leads a coalition army to defeat the American forces occupying France. <br>
<br>
After Canda's army &lt;cough&gt; defeats the military forces of the United States, and the US signs treaty which provides for peace under several conditions, one of which is to allow Canadian inspectors access all sites capable of creating, storing, or utilizing weapons of mass destruction. Another provision severely limits US exports of wine and cheese.<br>
<br>
Fast forward a few years, the US tells Canada to bugger off, kicks their inspectors out, and asks the world community why it's being &quot;Victimized&quot; by the Canadian war machine.  Meanwhile the US is giving sizeable covert donations to an organization of <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Heaven's Gate</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Idealists who's only intent is to cause fear and discontent throughout Canada.<br>
<br>
Seven years later the Stanly Cup is being contested in Calgary to a packed house. During the first period two DC-9's come crashing through the roof of the center killing thousands of Canadians. After an extensive investigation the incident is traced back to a group of <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Heaven's Gate</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> fundamentalists funded by a number of sources. <br>
<br>
An inteligence report shows pictures of a meeting between a high ranking US general and one of the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Heaven's Gate</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> fund raisers. However, no link can be proven between the government and the the group.<br>
<br>
Meanwhile the US still refuses to allow Canadian inspectors into the country, and continues rebuilding it's military, while strenuously denying any wrong doing...<br>
<br>
Okay, now the Canadian inspectors should be allowed.<br>
